frameDefinitions: An Agent makes use of a Means (either an action or a (system of) entities standing in for the action) in order to achieve a Purpose.
This frame concerns people's knowledge or skill in certain domains.
An Activity takes some Time_length to complete.
A Theme is in a stable position with respect to a Location.
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .

A Manner describes general or specific characteristics of an event in one of three ways:  First, it can refer to how a Comparison_event transpires, absent the influence of an entity (e.g. 'the way you talk').
frameExamples: The primary <t>means</t> of gas detection is mass spectroscopy .
FE Layer-1: He is an <t>experienced</t> programmer.
Our offices are <t>located</t> about two miles south of I-85 .
The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
He completed the task in a fervent <t>manner</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: The Agent uses the Means to acheive a Purpose.
The action performed by the Agent.
The goal or purpose of the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> uses the <fen>Means</fen>.
The person whose expertise is assessed.
<fen>Skill</fen> identifies the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s talent or ability to do things with one's hand or body.
The area of knowledge (as opposed to a practical skill) in which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> 's experience is assessed.
A  product of behavior that shows the <fen>Protagonist</fen>'s skill or lack of skill.

This frame element can only occur in place of a skill expression. It refers to the prototypical patient in an action involving the Protagonist. For instance, in the following sentence  the children are experts at some (contextually given) action such as rolling the hoops.

<fex name='Protagonist'>Some children</fex> <m>were</m> <fex name='Degree'>quite</fex> <t>expert</t> <fex name='Focal_participant'>with wooden hoops</fex>.
This frame element denotes a role in which the protagonist has developed his expertise.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Protagonist</fen> has the expertise.
The event which requires some <fen>Time_length</fen> for completion.
The amount of time required for the <fen>Activity</fen>.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Time_length</fen> from the norm.
The individual who performs the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Activity</fen> takes place.
An entity which is at a particular Location
A salient entity that the <fen>Theme</fen> is located with respect to.
The time at which the <fen>Theme</fen> is at the <fen>Location</fen>.
The location (generally presumed to be known to the interlocutor) with respect to which the location of the <fen>Theme</fen> can be understood.
An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.

The <fen>Comparison_event</fen> is the principal event being characteriszed by the <fen>Manner</fen>. The <fen>Manner</fen> of this <fen>Comparison_event</fen> is often used in comparison with the <fen>Foreground_event</fen>.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> that is associated with or directly responsible for the <fen>Comparison_activity</fen>.
The description of the <fen>Comparison_event</fen> or <fen>Comparison_activity</fen>.
A description of the <fen>Manner</fen>.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> conducts or engages in the <fen>Comparison_activity</fen> that is being described.
listRoleExamples: A skillful <fex>advertising campaign</fex> persuaded voters that his opponent was soft on crime.
His prowess <fex>as a surgeon</fex> is impressive.
<fex>A heavy contact to the opponent 's face</fex> may not merit just a verbal warning
